base_value: The library has one service standard for all channels (phone, e-mail, fax, and in person.) As an Internal service with relatively low number of client transactions, the Library assesses client satisfaction informally (feedback from clients, user comments, etc.) Total volume across all channels for ISC and CIRNAC was 221. Disaggregated data on performance against service standards is currently not available.
comp_value: Total number that met the service standard target = number of requests determined within service standards.

base_value: The Public Enquiries Contact Centre has one service standard for all channels. We are currently only able to measure the volume that meets the target with precision for the phone channel. The phone system we use (Rogers VCC) measures how many calls answered within a certain threshold which is currently a target of 80% of calls answered within 90 seconds. The total annual volume includes enquiries in all channels.is 58,688 but this number includes enquires received by phone, e-mail fax and in-person. The volume meeting target of 100% applies on to enquiries answered by phone (45,224 total) in terms of the general service standard of 3 days, not the phone performance target which only applies to phone enquiries. Of the phone calls we answered, 92.% were answered within target.
comp_value: Data source: Jordan's Principle Case Management System, extracted on September 18, 2025 and may not align with other analyses

base_value: Jordan's Principle service standards have been defined by the CHRT Orders and are the same across all intake platforms. This service standard is for urgent individual requests (12 hours). Jordan's Principle is a demand-driven initiative that has experienced exponential growth far exceeding expectations and the capacity to keep up with the expanding demand.
comp_value: Total annual volume = number of requests determined. Total number that met the service standard target = number of requests determined within service standards. Data source: Jordan's Principle Case Management System, extracted on September 18, 2025 and may not align with other analyse

base_value: Les normes de service du principe de Jordan ont été définies par les ordonnances du TCDP et sont les mêmes sur toutes les plateformes d’admission. Cette norme de service est destinée aux demandes individuelles urgentes (12 heures). Le Principe de Jordan est une initiative axée sur la demande qui a connu une croissance exponentielle dépassant de loin les attentes et la capacité de répondre à la demande croissante.
comp_value: Volume annuel total = nombre de demandes déterminées. Nombre total ayant respecté la norme de service = nombre de demandes déterminées selon les normes de service. Source des données : Système de gestion des cas du Principe de Jordan, extrait le 18 septembre 2025, et il se peut que ces données ne correspondent pas à d’autres analyses.
